This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new approach for federated learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. It also discusses the training convergence and efficiency of the proposed approach, which are important topics in machine learning research. 

It may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it deals with the challenges of utilizing network capacities between nodes in a decentralized setting. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it discusses the distribution of network capacities between nodes in a federated learning scenario. 

It may also fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it proposes a new approach for optimizing the training process in a distributed system. 

Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it discusses the emerging concern about data privacy and security in federated learning.
